Title: The Priory of the Orange Tree (The Roots of Chaos, #1)
Author: Samantha Shannon
My Review:
Has lots of cool ideas going for it, with regards to magic, characters and creatures. In terms of world building, Shannon falls into some stale clichés mirroring feudal Japan and China as the clearly foreign 'Eastern' nations and Roman Catholic western nations.

Pacing seems off too, major conflicts have decent buildup but are resolved way too quickly.
